GetValue()

Get value of the FDFField

Declaration

Returns
Type Description
Obj

the value of the Field (the value of its /V key) or NULL if the value is not specified.

Remarks

The format of field’s value varies depending on the field type. Set the value of the FDFField (the value of the field's /V key). the value of the field (the value of its /V key) or NULL if the value is not specified.
in order to remove/erase the existing value use SetValue(SDF::Null)
